FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1774314171
OL,3,CChancellor urged not to 'leave
OL,4,Ccitizens in the cold' over rising bills
OL,6,FSNP economy spokesman Dave Doogan
OL,7,Fpointed to the support announced in
OL,8,FIreland on Monday, comparing the
OL,9,Factions taken by the government in
OL,10,FDublin to the lack of powers available
OL,11,Fto the Scottish Government to support
OL,12,Fpeople.
OL,14,FOil prices spiked following the US-led
OL,15,Foffensive, but have started to come
OL,16,Fdown, reaching 104 dollars a barrel on
OL,17,FMonday.
OL,19,FMr Doogan said: "While independent
OL,20,FIreland acts, Westminster can't once
OL,21,Fagain leave citizens in the cold.
OL,26,@{D@QOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1774314171
OL,3,CChancellor urged not to 'leave
OL,4,Ccitizens in the cold' over rising bills
OL,6,F"The economic reality is that people
OL,7,Fsimply can't afford another massive
OL,8,Fhike in their energy and fuel bills `
OL,9,Ftherefore the political reality must
OL,10,Fbe that it can't be allowed to happen.
OL,12,F"Unfortunately, people won't hold
OL,13,Ftheir breath when it comes to
OL,14,Fexpecting real support from
OL,15,FWestminster ` the only hope of
OL,16,Fchanging Scotland's story is by taking
OL,17,Four energy into our own hands through
OL,18,Fthe fresh start of independence.
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1774314171
OL,3,CChancellor urged not to 'leave
OL,4,Ccitizens in the cold' over rising bills
OL,6,F"With families and businesses
OL,7,Fstruggling to fill up at the pumps and
OL,8,Ffacing the real fear of energy bills
OL,9,Fspiking again, they know that Keir
OL,10,FStarmer has already broken his promise
OL,11,Fto cut energy bills by #300 and the
OL,12,FLabour Party have barely lifted a
OL,13,Ffinger when people are badly in need
OL,14,Fof help."
OL,16,FWith just seven weeks to go before the
OL,17,FHolyrood elections in May, Mr Doogan
OL,18,Ftouted Scottish independence as a way
OL,19,Ffor ministers in Edinburgh to take
OL,20,Fcontrol over energy generated in
OL,21,FScotland.
OL,26,@nD@AOUvD@IO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1774314171
OL,3,CChancellor urged not to 'leave
OL,4,Ccitizens in the cold' over rising bills
OL,6,FHe said: "It is clearer by the day
OL,7,Fthat no Westminster government can be
OL,8,Ftrusted with our energy wealth.
OL,10,F"It is Scotland's energy ` and the
OL,11,Fbenefits of it should be felt by the
OL,12,Fpeople of Scotland.
OL,14,F"Our nearest neighbour, Ireland ` a
OL,15,Fsmall, independent country in the
OL,16,FEuropean Union ` has the wealth and
OL,17,Fthe will to help its citizens when
OL,18,Fthey need it most.
OL,26,@nD@JOUrD@AOUvD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30306
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1774314171
OL,3,CChancellor urged not to 'leave
OL,4,Ccitizens in the cold' over rising bills
OL,6,F"An independent, energy-rich Scotland
OL,7,Fcould act in the very same way for all
OL,8,Four people.
OL,10,F"With full control over our energy
OL,11,Fresources, we can bring energy bills
OL,12,Fdown."
OL,14,FSpeaking to a Parliamentary Liaison
OL,15,FCommittee on Monday, Sir Keir said: "I
OL,16,Fcan reassure the committee that we
OL,17,Fhaven't any meaningful concerns about
OL,18,Fenergy supplies. Obviously, the price
OL,19,Ffluctuates daily.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@AOUtD@FO]wD@eOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30307
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1774314171
OL,3,CChancellor urged not to 'leave
OL,4,Ccitizens in the cold' over rising bills
OL,6,F"For household energy bills, it is
OL,7,Fimportant for me to reiterate that
OL,8,Fthey will be cut because of the
OL,9,Fmeasures we took in the budget last
OL,10,Fyear and then held until the end of
OL,11,FJune.
OL,13,F"And I know that for many members of
OL,14,Fthe public, the question they've been
OL,15,Fasking is, does that still hold even
OL,16,Fif the conflict goes on? And the
OL,17,Fanswer to that question is yes. So
OL,18,Fthere's comfort there for households."
OL,26,@nD@AOUuD@AOUzD@fO]
